Three teenagers - one female and two males - are to be tried as adults after allegedly luring a 16-year-old boy into a shed, shooting him with a BB gun, attacking him with a crow bar and carving a swastika into his forehead with a box cutter.

Jenna Jean Montgomery, 15, Blue Christian Kalmbach, 15, and Jess Taylor, 17, pleaded not guilty to attacking 16-year-old Dustyn Murrain and were each held on a $3 million bail bond at a court hearing yesterday.

A fourth suspect, an unnamed 14-year-old male, who is also accused of taking part in the assault on the schoolboy, will be tried as a juvenile on less serious charges.

