Police now suspect the foursome launched the gruesome attack, which took place on February 10 behind a house in Southeast Portland, in a bid to steal the victim's skateboard and cash.

Police also suggested the victim had been perceived as a bully and the four saw the attack as retaliation.

The victim, told police he was lured to the shed by Miss Montgomery, a fellow David Douglas High School student, who he had met earlier in the day.

Murrain said he was invited to meet the girl at Southeast 122nd Avenue and Powell Boulevard, according to prosecutor Christopher Ramras.

